license_test.py is a simple naive bayes classifier for determining 
whether a file contains a license or not.

Training data:
	Two files containing the paths of the positive and negative training files 
are needed. One line for each path.  The standard license templates can be used for 
the positive training data.  The following command can be used to create the needed
training files.

List of files positive for licenses:
	find ../Licenses/ -type f -not \( -regex ".*meta$$" \)  -not \( -wholename "*.svn*" \) > pos.txt

List of files negative for licenses:
	find ../Training/License_Test -type f -not \( -regex ".*meta$$" \)  -not \( -wholename "*.svn*" \) > neg.txt

NOTE : $PYTHONPATH should include the utils directory contained in the parent of this directory.
NOTE : $PATH must include . or the License_Test directory

Usage: license_test.py -y yes_files -n no_files [ -h ] test_files...

Options:
  -h, --help         show this help message and exit
  -y YES, --yes=YES  A text file with the paths to the yes training files.
  -n NO, --no=NO     A text file with the paths to the no training files.
  --lw=LW            Left window plus 1. Must be > 0.
  --rw=RW            Right window plus 1. Must be > 0
  --pr=PR            Prior probability of seeing a yes file. Must be between 0
                     and 1

Use --lw=2 --rw=2 --pr=0.6

Example:
	export PYTHONPATH=../utils/
	find ../Licenses/ -type f -not \( -regex ".*meta$$" \)  -not \( -wholename "*.svn*" \) > pos.txt
	find ../Training/License_Test/ -type f -not \( -regex ".*meta$$" \)  -not \( -wholename "*.svn*" \) > neg.txt
	python license_test.py --lw=2 --rw=2 --pr=0.6 -y pos.txt -n neg.txt `find /usr/share/doc/ -type f`
